'''Belemir''' (born {{FA|339}}) was a [[Men|man]] of the [[House of Bëor]].
== History ==
Belemir was the son of [[Beldir]] and husband to [[Adanel]] of the [[House of Hador|House of Marach]]. He fathered [[Beren (son of Belemir)|Beren]], grandfather of [[Beren|Beren Erchamion]], hero of the First Age.<ref>{{WJ|West}}, ''Commentary, (i) The House of Bëor'', p. 231</ref>

There was great love between he and his younger kinswoman [[Andreth]], and she dwelt long in his house. While there, Andreth learned much of the lore of the folk of [[Marach]] from Adanel.<ref>{{MR|P4a}}</ref>

In {{FA|409}}, [[Finrod]] was a guest in his house and [[Athrabeth Finrod ah Andreth|held a long debate]] with Andreth.<ref>{{MR|P4c}}</ref>

